Now, now, I am but an ordinary man!
Perhaps just the slightest bit craftier than most.
My magical bullets may be of some help to you... But do be careful, I only have so many!

mstSvtComment.comment:
Height/Weight: 175cm, 68kg
Origin: Sherlock Holmes Series
Region: All of Europe
Alignment: Chaotic-Evil
Gender: Male
Call me Mr. Dandy! (Not gonna happen)

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 2 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
A professor of mathematics and Sherlock Holmes's most formidable adversary.
Though he only appears in three books, usually as little more than a description offered by Holmes, this malevolently charismatic man enjoyed enormous support thanks to his machinations in Holmes's final (later made un-final) case.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 3 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
A brilliant philosopher and certified genius.
Dubbed "The Napoleon of crime" by Holmes, he established a criminal network that spanned all of Europe while working as a professor of mathematics.
According to details revealed in the original books, he served as a kind of criminal consultant.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 4 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
『The Dynamics of an Asteroid』
Rank: A+
NP Type: Anti-Army
Range: 1-99　Maximum Targets: 100
The Ultimate Crime.
A Noble Phantasm that manifests the ultimate destruction Moriarty seeks: that of the entire planet.
Though this NP remains at Anti-Army scale due to the limitations of the Servant container, it would expand to Anti-City and Anti-Nation if his power were to grow.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 5 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
A Fused Servant who has absorbed the Phantom Spirit "Der Freischütz," gaining his power to fire magic bullets.
In the play "The Marksman," a hunter sells his soul to the devil in exchange for six magic bullets that will always hit their target.
However, the seventh bullet will hit a target of the devil's own choosing... Someone whose death will plunge the hunter into despair.
It will be revealed when you complete a certain quest.

[id 202310_0_B050]True Name sealed. Pseudo Noble Phantasm, release.
[id 202310_0_B051]Time for your punishment!
[id 202310_0_B052]Wonderful... The world is full of destruction!
[id 202310_0_B053]Fwahahaha!
I shall accept.
It's an honor.
Let us begin. I must warm up, so kindly wait a moment!
Good. As a representative of the middle-aged Servants, I shall do my best.
Ack!? My hip! My hip just cracked!
Good. A flawless victory.
Ungh!
Impossible...!
We've come to a dead-end...
Sorry, but we need to retreat...
Jack...
Queen...
King...
Then, the Joker.
Getting stronger is a good thing. Mhmm!
[id 202310_0_G020]Ah, so this is ascension. [id 202310_0_G021]Alas, I don't seem to have time for a wardrobe change.
[id 202310_0_G030]A wardrobe change. [id 202310_0_G031]I suppose such a thing isn't so exciting when it's an old man, though. [id 202310_0_G032]I assume you're in it for the skills. Am I correct?

[id 202310_0_G040]My wardrobe has become quite elaborate, my level has increased, [delay 3.8]and my back has started creaking. [id 202310_0_G041]But no! I'm fine! [id 202310_0_G042]I shall pay you back for raising me up to this point!
[id 202310_0_G050]I'm impressed you raised me up to this point without knowing my True Name! [id 202310_0_G051]What drew you to me? [id 202310_0_G052]Well, even I'm not rotten enough to betray you.
Getting stronger is a good thing. Mhmm!
Happy birthday! Youth fades in the blink of an eye. Enjoy it while you still can.
It seems there is an event going on right now. Are you going to participate?
All right. Shall we get going?
As your elder, I suppose my job is to show you the way. Mind you, I may lead you to evil.
Of course, you are an ace. No, no. I don't have anything up my sleeve. Really. Hahahaha.
Hm. I don't suppose this would give anything away... I love mathematics from the bottom of my heart. I find numbers soothing.
What I dislike...? Hahaha, let me think... What if I said deerstalker hats?
The Grail possesses great power, but that's all. It's no more or less than that, which makes it easy to account for in my calculations.
Let's work well together, Master!
True Names are not to be lightly revealed. That's how it goes.
What's wrong, Master? I will always be by your side.
...Do you like riddles? If you didn't, you wouldn't be raising a Servant who hasn't revealed his True Name up to this point.
Ah, you impress me. I cannot yet reveal my True Name, but I promise you that one day, I shall disclose it to you. I am a dishonest man, yes, but...well, that is the most I can think to say for now.

Hahahaha!
You must be a peculiar Master to have summoned me!
My Class is Archer.
For now, I shall hold off on revealing my True Name!
But I am strong. That much I can guarantee!
Oh, magical bullet!
I shall inquire!
Destruction!
How are you enjoying your extermination?

[id 202300_0_B050]Noble Phantasm, release.
[id 202300_0_B051]My final problem, the ultimate crime, shall be proven here.
[id 202300_0_B052]The Dynamics of an...Asteroid!
Trivial.
Allow me to summon my spider.
Let us begin our lesson. Get your paper and pen!
You have the honor of fighting Moriarty.
Ideally, I would win the battle before it began. Then again, a contest of strength isn't so bad, either.
I suppose not everything can happen as calculated. But the outcome is still interesting.
Ungh!
I missed!
It is your victory. You should be proud.
Reichenbach...back to that waterfall...
Jack...
Queen...
King...
Then, the Joker.
Ah, to mature!
[id 202300_0_G020]Fwahahahaha, Ascension is good. [id 202300_0_G021]Very good. It gets the blood pumping!

[id 202300_0_G030]I shall now change my wardrobe. [id 202300_0_G031]Hm, I appear to have gained some weight. [id 202300_0_G032]Fwahahahaha!
[id 202300_0_G033]I suppose that's no laughing matter...

[id 202300_0_G040]I dance both gracefully and cruelly.
[id 202300_0_G041]I am a spider, a butterfly, a humble professor, [id 202300_0_G042]and a criminal genius.

[id 202300_0_G050]I do not intend to lead you down the path of evil.
[id 202300_0_G051]But the temptation to be able to walk alongside you is difficult to ignore.
[id 202300_0_G052]Thank you, Master.
It is your birthday! Celebrate! We must celebrate! Perhaps I should offer you a deerstalker hat as a gift!
It seems there is an event going on right now. Are you going to participate?
All right. Shall we get going?
I am the head of an evil organization, after all! As you are my Master, that makes you its true leader!
If I promised to serve faithfully, I'd look suspicious. If I promised to serve unfaithfully, that would confirm everyone's suspicions. It's tough being a villain!
What I like? Obviously, that would be planning something sinister! It is exciting when everything goes according to calculation, and just as exciting when things do not!
What I dislike? Well, obviously, that would be Sherlock! Curse you, Holmes! Why am I middle-aged, while you get to be a devastatingly handsome young man!? Unforgivable!
The Grail possesses great power, but nothing more. What's important is the variable X.
Oh? Do you have business with Moriarty?
Very well. Let us begin our mathematics lesson!

Very well. Let us begin our lesson in evil organization operations!
Wha...not interested?
Let me see, your aptitude for evil...is lacking! You are the embodiment of all that is good! What exactly are you? It's all so fascinating!
You are good, yet you do not hate evil. You may be tormented by evil, but you carry on doing good. Listen carefully: no matter what others tell you, that is a wonderful thing.
Ah, I did not know Rider was here. I know getting him to open up is difficult, but try your best.
Ah, Dantès. Fwahahaha. I imagine it is quite a surprise for you, one who uses evil to achieve justice, to see someone like me here! Hey! Hello? Answer me!
Ah, Jekyll. Haha, do not be so cautious. We are both Servants, after all. Let's work together harmoniously. Yes, harmoniously.
Hm! That's Sherlock Holmes over there! Right then, Master, throw a tomato or something at him!

My name is James Moriarty!
I am both a professor, and the head of an evil organization!
Fwahahahaha!
No need to worry. If you leave everything to me, taking over the world once or twice will be child's play!

[talker 103100 1 0 "Electric Steam feat. Papa" 0][talker 202300 0 0 hoge -300][talker 501100 1 0 hoge 300]Fran: How's that!?
Babbage: Hm. Steam engine's in good shape.
Professor M: My evil tricks are in top form as well!

[talker 103100 1 0 "Electric Steam feat. Papa" 0][talker 202300 0 0 hoge -300][talker 501100 1 0 hoge 300]Fran: And we go away!
Babbage: That would be, "Away we go."
Professor M: Come now, both of you! We're going away!

[talker 103100 1 0 "Electric Steam feat. Papa" 0][talker 202300 0 0 hoge -300][talker 501100 1 0 hoge 300]Fran: Lightning! Fwahahaha!
Babbage: My dear child. I do not recommend doing impressions of Nikola Tesla.
Professor M: Right. If you end up too like him, you'll make Papa sad.

[talker 103100 1 0 "Electric Steam feat. Papa" 0][talker 202300 0 0 hoge -300][talker 501100 1 0 hoge 300]Professor M: Ah, if the order of the day is a jailbreak, leave it to me!
However, I must admit that I've never been caught myself...
Babbage: Now that you mention it, that's true...
Professor, does that mean you're a complete amateur at this?
Fran: Dig, dig, dig...

[talker 103100 1 0 "Electric Steam feat. Papa" 0][talker 202300 0 0 hoge -300][talker 501100 1 0 hoge 300]Professor M: All right. Let's name the tunnels Dick, Harry, and Tom.
Babbage: Is that just your way of telegraphing that not all of us will make it out?
Professor M: It's not our problem!
Fran: I think that's why Papa's no good.

[talker 103100 1 0 "Electric Steam feat. Papa" 0][talker 202300 0 0 hoge -300][talker 501100 1 0 hoge 300]Professor M: What we need is a spoon, glue, and a rock hammer...
Ah, jailbreaks are so fun.
Fran: Every man's dream?
Professor M: Dream for a rebel, my Fran. Fuwahahahaha!

Fran: We won big!
Professor M: Yaaay!
Babbage: All right, we need to make adjustments. Where's my wrench...

Fran: We won! (Victory sign)
Babbage: Do not lower your guard. Once you win, tighten your helmet's strap, as the saying goes.
Professor M: Unfortunately, I can't for the life of me tell where your strap is.

Professor M: Excellent. A perfect victory! Oh yes, this is going to make me rich...
Babbage: I sense something disturbing afoot.
Fran: Earning money is a good thing.
The more money you have to make your escape with, the better.

Professor M: Crawling through the sewer pipes is quite romantic for us villains.
Fran: W-we're no villains!
The only villain around here is Papa!

Professor M: That's why I said this: “Behold, this grand physique! It is like tempered steel!”
Yes, indeed, that is what I said!
Babbage: Wait. Where are you going with that?
Professor M: Have you not heard the phrase
“Stay tuned for the next episode”?
Fran: Rrrrrrrr...
Get back to work, you two!

Professor M: Owww! My back, my back! It made a sound backs should not make!
Miss Fran, would you mind bending me back into shape?
Fran: Okay, Papa!
Babbage: Dodgey professor, asking her to realign your back with her weapon is extremely dangerous.

Professor M: We won. We're victorious!
We're ultra-rich! Yahooo!
Fran: I did it!
Did you see me!?
Babbage: Indeed, you should be commended.
What's more, this proves without a doubt that steam engines are the strongest form of power.
